&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top: 4.8pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 6.0pt; margin-left: 0cm; line-height: 115%; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 115%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;With Hitler&apos;s rise to power in 1933, Zweig&apos;s books were condemned in Germany and later banned. Fascism was on the rise in Austria as well, and in 1934 the police came to search Zweig&apos;s home. Zweig left his house, never to return again. It was then that he divorced his first wife and moved to London. &amp;#160;Later he wrote that at that time he sensed the heavy clouds that were hanging above. At this point, Zweig dispersed his papers and sold his manuscript collection.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
