&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 115%; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;After graduating in 1906, and completing his year of training, Kafka started to work as an insurance officer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 115%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160; Kafka called this his &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Brotberuf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt; or &quot;Bread Job&quot;, and constantly bemoaned the fact that he did not have enough time for his real passion: writing. Despite this, he wrote almost incessantly, writing stories, novels and letters. Still, he was extremely critical of his works. As a result, many of his texts remained unfinished. This is the case regarding his three famous novels, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The Castle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The Trial&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The Missing Man&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;, as well as a number of stories which were found by his close friend, the writer Max Brod. One of his most famous stories is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The Metamorphosis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;, which tells of the miserable Gregor Samsa who wakes up one morning to find himself transformed into a huge insect.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
