&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;In 1148, Cordoba was taken over by the intolerant&lt;i&gt; &lt;/i&gt;dynasty of the &lt;i&gt;Muwahhidun&lt;/i&gt; (Almohads), who by then ruled most of the Maghreb as well. The Almohads deprived the non-Muslim communities of their previous rights and persecuted them with threats of forced conversion or deportation. The Maimonides family, like many others, left Cordoba and began an extended period of wandering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

