&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left; line-height: normal; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;In his diary, Elimelech Basch described his family&apos;s last days. The family debated what to do until the last moment, after the Germans had already entered the town:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left; line-height: normal; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&quot;I argued with my wife that she shouldn&apos;t clean and paint for (the holiday of) Passover, but she continued her work as usual saying that as long as we live we should hope for the good and God will choose to do as he sees fit. My son Isaac, seeing my great anxiety, said that I should buy a gun and shoot all the members of our family&quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left; line-height: normal; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&#8230;&quot; I watched my children play and wept, who knows what will happen to them?&quot; &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

