&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The miniature makes use of religious symbolism &#8211; Sultan Selim I, on horseback, is dressed in the mantle of the Prophet Muhammad, implying that it is he who defends true Islam, that is, the Sunni tradition. Above him, a flag flies with the legend, &#8220;Victory from Allah and redemption at hand.&#8221; There is no indication that the Shah and his army are Muslims, but rather, they are dressed like pre-Islamic Persian soldiers.&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
