&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: -17.05pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: -7.1pt; line-height: 115%; text-autospace: none;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 115%; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Literally meaning &quot;tradition&quot; or &quot;reception&quot;, Kabbalah is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 115%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;the traditional term for medieval esoteric Judaism and for Jewish mysticism. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 115%; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Although it has much earlier roots, the term Kabbalah usually refers to the discipline which developed in Provence and Catalu&#241;a from the second half of the 12th century onward&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 115%; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;Following the expulsion of the Jews from Spain in 1492, a new trend in Kabbalah, Lurianic Kabbalah, developed in Safed, a town in 16th-century Ottoman Palestine, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoHyperlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;called by the Jews, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;The Land of Israel&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;.&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

