&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left; line-height: normal; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Elimelech Basch&apos;s eldest daughter, Bluma (Perhiya), was the only member of the Basch family to survive the Holocaust. &amp;#160;&amp;#160;Bluma immigrated to Israel, changed her name to Perhiya and built a new family. &amp;#160;Perhiya has three children, many grandchildren and a newborn great granddaughter. &amp;#160;She is now 87 years old and is still an active volunteer in her hometown, Lydda (Lod). &amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

