&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;The last census before the German occupation, held in January 1941, reported that there were 2,150 Jewish residents in Tiachiv. They made up 20% of the total population of the town.&amp;#160; Many of the Jews were merchants; others were craftsmen, agricultural workers and farmers.&amp;#160; The Jewish community was, like most Jewish communities in Eastern Europe, a religiously observant, Orthodox community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
