&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The roots of the Kabbalah go back to early esoteric Jewish literature such as the&lt;i&gt; Heavenly Sanctuaries Literature &lt;/i&gt;(&lt;i&gt;Hekhalot&lt;/i&gt; lietrature), &lt;i&gt;Work of the Chariot &lt;/i&gt;(&lt;i&gt;Ma&apos;aseh Merkava&lt;/i&gt;) and &lt;i&gt;The Book of &lt;/i&gt;Creation (&lt;i&gt;Sefer Yetzira&lt;/i&gt;); this literature itself originates in earlier sources going back to the 1st-2nd centuries.&lt;i&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
