--&gt;
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Being of Spanish origin, Yahuda took a special interest in collecting material pertaining to the history of the Jews in Spain. Among these are documents from the Jewish Community in Aragon, including a privilege granted by King Alfonso V of Aragon (1416-1438) to the nobleman Berenguer de Bardaxi , granting him permission to settle 30-40 Jewish families on his lands in Oliete, south of Zaragoza.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
