&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
&lt;!--
body {
font-family: Arial;  font-size: small;  background: #ffffff;  color: #000000;
}
p {
margin-top: 0pt;  margin-bottom: 0pt;
}
--&gt;
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;This map was drawn in the Netherlands, following Ortelius&apos;s map of the Holy Land around 1600. The anonymous artist added to Ortelius&apos; map a series of illustrations, including Jonah being tossed to the mouth of the big fish and Israelite figures crossing the desert. At the bottom right the twelve tribes are encamped in the Sinai Desert, and on the bottom right the Grotto of the Nativity in Bethlehem is depicted. Interestingly, the North in the compass rose is pointing to the south!&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;generator&quot; content=&quot;EditLive! 7.6.2.10&quot; /&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;generator&quot; content=&quot;TheBrain 7.0.4.5&quot; /&gt;
&lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;Content-Type&quot; content=&quot;text/html; charset=UTF-8&quot; /&gt;
&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
&lt;!--
body {
font-family: Arial;  font-size: small;  background: #ffffff;  color: #000000;
}
p {
margin-top: 0pt;  margin-bottom: 0pt;
}
--&gt;
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoPlainText&quot; style=&quot; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;This lovely hand-drawn map was drawn in the 19th century by an artist who claims that he copied it from the famous Jewish scholar, the Vilna Gaon (1720-1797).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoPlainText&quot; style=&quot; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;The map follows an ancient tradition of mapping the borders of Land of Israel, as described in Numbers 34. This tradition commenced with Rashi, the greatest Jewish Biblical commentator, who lived in France in the 11th century.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoPlainText&quot; style=&quot; text-align: justify; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Later tradition added the allotments of the 12 tribes, and cities and settlements which are represented here as European houses with tiled roofs. Jerusalem is depicted prominently with a tower beside it bearing the inscription &quot;The Temple&quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;generator&quot; content=&quot;EditLive! 7.6.2.10&quot; /&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;generator&quot; content=&quot;TheBrain 7.0.4.5&quot; /&gt;
&lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;Content-Type&quot; content=&quot;text/html; charset=UTF-8&quot; /&gt;
&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
&lt;!--
body {
font-family: Arial;  font-size: small;  background: #ffffff;  color: #000000;
}
p {
margin-top: 0pt;  margin-bottom: 0pt;
}
--&gt;
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;King Solomon&apos;s palace and the First Temple depicted in detail: The Temple Courtyard drawn according to Josephus&apos; description, the Ark and the Cherubim, the High Priest, the Candelabrum and the Table of the Showbread, as well as the Sacrificial Altar in front of the Temple.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
