&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #3F3F3F;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;The National Library of Israel houses various Torah scrolls. The Torah we present here, which belonged to the Kahal Shalom Synagogue in Rhodes, is actually one of the less impressive to look at; it is, in fact, disintegrating and according to our conservationist - is actually beyond repair.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #3F3F3F;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Although the National Library of Israel possesses finer ones - in a much better state of preservation, we chose to present this one because of the fascinating story of its wanderings throughout the Mediterranean and the hardships it encountered until its arrival at our library in the summer of 1999.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #3F3F3F;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;This story represents the history of the Jewish people throughout the ages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: rgb(63, 63, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Photograph of Coat: The inscription reads &apos;Donated in memory of our dear brothers who died in sanctification of the divine name, by Hayyim and Lilly Noterika&apos;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
