&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; line-height: 115%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;In spring 1914, Franz Kafka was about to go to Berlin in order to be betrothed to his first fianc&#233;e, Felice Bauer (whom he never married). In this letter Kafka invites Lise Weltsch, the young lady who was photographed with him and other friends from Vienna, to meet him and his fianc&#233;e in Berlin. Kafka expresses his delight at leaving his parents&apos; home in Prague where he was residing then, and coming to spend some time in Berlin.&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

