&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; background-color: #ffffff;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;The Torah used in the Synagogue is copied on specially prepared vellum or parchment by a scribe called Sofer Stam who specializes in copying sacred texts according to the ritual laws; it is sewn together in one piece and rolled up around two rollers with handles.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

