&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;LTR&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: black;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Zweig studied Philosophy at the University of Vienna and in 1904 earned a doctoral degree. In those student years Zweig published his first book of poetry, as well as various pieces in the most prestigious newspaper in Vienna, the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Neue Freie Presse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;whose editor was Theodore Herzl, the leading figure in the Jewish National Movement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: black;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;. Having proven his talent, Zweig was exempted from working in the family business.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
