&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;In the following decade Zweig moved constantly between Vienna, Berlin, Paris and Brussels. During this period he made the acquaintance of famous poets, writers and artists such as Auguste Rodin, Rainer Maria Rilke, Romain Rolland, W.B. Yeats, Pirandello and many others. It was during this time that he started to write novellas and dramas which soon became very popular.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

