&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Benjamin to Gershom Scholem, Paris, 20 March 1933:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In this letter, written less than a month later, Benjamin mentions to Scholem that he intends to stay in Ibiza for a while, a plan that materialized somewhat later.&amp;#160; He also informs him of a new manuscript he would soon send. Benjamin notes that &quot;this text is especially meant to adorn your archive&quot;, probably because it contains references to Hebrew as well. The typescript, which bears the title &lt;i&gt;&#220;ber die Sprache &#252;berhaupt und &#252;ber die Sprache des Menschen&lt;/i&gt;, &lt;i&gt;also hebr&#228;isch&lt;/i&gt; (&lt;i&gt;About language as such, and about the language of people, as well as about Hebrew&lt;/i&gt;) was indeed sent and can be found in the Walter Benjamin Archives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

